    • setOffset

      void setOffset(int x, int z)
      Set the offset applied to values when storing and reading to keep the values within -1024 to 1023. Uses default y offset of 128 to allow -64 -> 320 world height use.
      Parameters:
      x - x offset
      z - z offset
      Since:
      2.9.2

    • setOffset

      void setOffset(int x, int y, int z)
      Set the offset applied to values when storing and reading to keep the x and z values within -1024 to 1023. Y values require keeping withing -256 and 255.
      Parameters:
      x - x offset
      y - y offset
      z - z offset
      Since:
      2.9.2
